==Starting off==
* '''Fred the Farmer:''' What are you doing on my land? You're not the one who keeps leaving all my gates open and letting out all my sheep, are you?
* {{tselect|Select an option}}
* {{topt|I'm looking for a quest.}}
** '''Player:''' I'm looking for a quest.
** {{tcond|On quest speedrunning worlds:}}
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' You're after a quest, you say? Well I don't have any here.
*** {{tbox|This quest is not available on Speedrunning Worlds.}}
*** {{Tact|end}}
** '''Fred the Farmer:''' You're after a quest, you say? Actually, I could do with a bit of help.
** '''Fred the Farmer:''' My sheep are getting mighty woolly. I'd be much obliged if you could shear them. And while you're at it, spin the wool for me too.
** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Yes, that's it. Bring me 20 balls of wool. And I'm sure I could sort out some sort of payment. Of course, there's the small matter of The Thing.
** {{tact|If the player already has 20 balls of wool in their inventory:}}
*** '''Player:''' In fact Fred, funnily enough, I actually have 20 balls of wool already on me.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Have you been shearing my sheep without permission!?
*** '''Player:''' No! Well, maybe... They just looked a little wooly! Surely you like a shave once in a while, too?
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' It's rude to shave another person without permission - don't be coming at me with them shears!
*** '''Player:''' I'm sorry, I'll ask permission next time.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' I guess no real 'arm was done. Hand the balls over and we can put this whole thing behind us.
*** {{Qact|Quest complete!}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** '''Player:''' What do you mean, The Thing?
** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Well now, no one has ever seen The Thing. That's why we call it The Thing, 'cos we don't know what it is.
** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Some say it's a black hearted shapeshifter, hungering for the souls of hard working decent folk like me. Others say it's just a sheep.
** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Well I don't have all day to stand around and gossip. Are you going to shear my sheep or what!
** {{tselect|Start the Sheep Shearer quest?}}
** {{topt|Yes.}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes, okay. I can do that.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Good! Now one more thing, do you actually know how to shear a sheep?
*** '''Player:''' Err. No, I don't know actually.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Well, first things first, you need a pair of shears. I've got some here you can use.
*** {{tbox|pic=Shears detail.png|Fred gives you a set of sharp shears.}}
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' You just need to go and use them on the sheep out in my field.
*** '''Player:''' Sounds easy!
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' That's what they all say!
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Some of the sheep don't like it too much... Persistence is the key.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Once you've collected some wool you can spin it into balls.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Do you know how to spin wool?
*** '''Player:''' I don't know how to spin wool, sorry.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Don't worry, it's quite simple!
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' The nearest Spinning Wheel can be found on the first floor of Lumbridge Castle.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' To get to Lumbridge Castle just follow the road east.
*** {{tbox|pic=7670 detail.png|This icon denotes a Spinning Wheel on the world map.}}
*** '''Player:''' Thank you!
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No.}}
*** '''Player:''' No, I'll give it a miss.
*** '''Fred the Farmer:''' Suit yourself.
*** {{tact|end}}
